<h2 id="section-top">Paediatrics services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=104613">London North West University Healthcare NHS Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent322e88493e604c4f9cd468ffead74b2e">
</div>
<p>Our paediatric team treat a range of conditions, as well as providing more general care for children. Our inpatient services for children are provided at Jack's Place, Level 3, Northwick Park Hospital, and we hold outpatient services for children at Central Middlesex, Ealing and Northwick Park Hospitals.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.lnwh.nhs.uk/service-finder/service/childrens-hospital-services-62/">Visit our website for more information on our paediatric services</a>.</p>
<p>Please note our A&amp;E department at Ealing Hospital does not have a children's A&amp;E. In case of an emergency and your child needs an ambulance, they will be taken to a hospital with a children's A&amp;E. This could be: West Middlesex, Hillingdon, <a href="https://www.lnwh.nhs.uk/service-finder/service/emergency-department-ae-133/">Northwick Park</a>, Chelsea and Westminster, or St. Mary’s hospitals, depending on your child’s needs.</p>
<p><strong>What to do if your child needs urgent care in Ealing:</strong></p>
<p>For both physical and mental health needs:</p>
<ul>
<li>In a life-threatening emergency call 999.</li>
<li>If it’s not a life-threatening situation, you can go to Ealing Hospital’s urgent care centre, visit/call your GP or call NHS 111.</li>
</ul></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
